message.content:
1. The study examined the effect of OSS on patients-per-provider-per-day (workload) among IMID-MLP.
2. The study also examined the effect of OSS on patients-per-provider-per-day (workload) among No-IMID.
3. The adjusted relative risk ratio (aRRR) for IMID-MLP was 1.21.
4. The p-value for IMID-MLP was 0.48.
5. The adjusted relative risk ratio (aRRR) for No-IMID was 0.90.
6. The p-value for No-IMID was 0.44.
7. The effect of OSS on patients-per-provider-per-day (workload) among IMID-MLP was not statistically significant.
8. The effect of OSS on patients-per-provider-per-day (workload) among No-IMID was not statistically significant.
